This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) because it presents a Python library for boosted statistical relational models, which are a type of machine learning model. Additionally, the library is adapted from the scikit-learn interface, which is a popular machine learning library in Python. 

The paper could also belong to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) because statistical relational models are often used in AI applications such as natural language processing and knowledge representation. 

The sub-category of databases (cs.DB) is also a possibility because statistical relational models are used in database applications such as data integration and entity resolution. 

The sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) is another possibility because statistical relational models are used in natural language processing tasks such as semantic parsing and relation extraction. 

Finally, the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) is a less likely possibility because statistical relational models have been used in security applications such as malware detection and intrusion detection.
